@candelabra
#end
:touch
#play tc-ge
The great candelabra gutters, its wax
long since run to grey stalactites.
For a moment the shadows lean toward
you. Then they settle back.
#end
    end

    stat at 29,20 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0x02 under Empty color 0x00
    oop
@steward
#end
:touch
#play tcdefg
Welcome, welcome, welcome. The Count
does so seldom entertain the living.
$-- The Ghost Steward
#zap touch
#end
:touch
Mind the doors, guest. WEST lies the
library; the iron key sleeps in a tome
there. EAST, the ruined chapel will
bless your stake. NORTH, the stairs go
DOWN -- but that door is locked until
you carry the iron key.
#zap touch
#end
:touch
The portraits watch you. They always
watch. Do try not to die in the hall;
the Count considers it untidy.
#end
    end
  end
end

