    oop
@crucifix
#end
:touch
#play tcefgec
An iron crucifix, black with age, hangs
crooked above the shattered altar.
The wood of the Cross has not rotted,
though everything around it has.
:more
#zap touch
#play tfa
You lay your hand on the cold iron.
For a moment the wind outside falls silent,
as if something distant flinched.
#end
    end
    stat at 29,12 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0x0F under Empty color 0x00
    oop
@altar
#end
:touch
#play tfec
The altar stone is split down its center.
Someone, long ago, carved words into it:
$WHAT SLEEPS BELOW FEARS ONLY THREE THINGS:
$THE CROSS, THE FLAME, AND THE COMING SUN.
Wax pools in the cracks. The candles here
burned down centuries past.
#end
    end
    stat at 31,12 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0x0F under Empty color 0x1B
    oop
@font
#end
:touch
#play tcgc
The holy water font is a basin of blue
marble, brimming still with clear water
that has never once gone stagnant.
:ask
#zap ask
Ripples move though no wind touches it.
Do you have a stake to bless?
!bless;Dip your wooden stake in the water.
!leave;Step back from the font.
#end
:bless
#play tcegcegc-c
You dip the sharpened stake into the font.
The water hisses; the wood drinks the light
and comes out pale, humming faintly.
A BLESSED STAKE is yours. The Count will
not like this at all.
#give gems 1
#zap ask
#end
:leave
The water settles. Your reflection is,
reassuringly, still there.
#end
    end
  end
end

