    oop
@tome
#end
:touch
#play tcd
A single crimson-bound tome sits apart from
the rest, its spine cracked with disuse.
The title is barely legible: "Ferro, Locke,
et Clavis" -- Of Iron, Locks, and Keys.
#play tc+e+g
You pry the cover open. It is hollow. Nestled
in the carved-out pages: a heavy iron key,
cold as a grave.
#give key white
#play tefgab+c
The key is yours. The iron door to the south
now seems worth revisiting.
#zap touch
:touch
The hollow tome is empty now.
It kept its secret longer than its author.
#end
    end

    stat at 31,9 element Object cycle 0 p1 cp437:0xEC under Normal color 0x68
    oop
@tomeb
#end
:touch
#play tc
Another crimson volume, but its pages are
solid and yellowed. Just a book, after all.
#end
    end

    stat at 19,12 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0x0F under Empty color 0x00
    oop
@ghost
#end
:touch
#play tc-c
A pale reading-clerk drifts between the stacks,
still shelving books two centuries dead.
He does not look up. His voice is dry paper:
"The key is bound in words, not lockmakers'
iron. Seek the crimson tome that speaks of
keys itself. It hides what it describes."
#play td-d
Then he fades, muttering catalogue numbers.
#end
    end

    stat at 19,18 element Object cycle 0 p1 cp437:0xF0 under Empty color 0x00
    oop
@plaque
#end
:touch
#play tf
A brass plaque, tarnished green with age:
$THE COUNT'S PRIVATE LIBRARY
Below it, scratched by a shakier hand:
"He never lends a book. Nor forgives a
reader who wanders too far south past the
iron door. Bring light. Bring courage."
#end
    end
    stat at 30,10 element Object cycle 3
    oop
    #end
    end
    stat at 31,10 element Object cycle 3
    oop
    #end
    end
  end
end

