@count
#end
:touch
#play tc.c.c.a-a-a-
The coffin lid grinds open. A pale lord unfolds
from the dark, eyes like two red coals.
So. Another warm little thing come to disturb
my rest. How CONSIDERATE of you to bring dinner.
:menu
#lock
!strike;Drive the stake through his heart
!water;Fling the vial of holy water
!flee;Back slowly toward the stairs
#unlock
#end
:flee
The Count laughs, a sound like coffin nails.
Running only tires the meat before I eat it.
#zap flee
The doors have sealed. There is only forward now.
#zap flee
No exit. No dawn. Only me.
#unlock
#restart
:water
#if holy #blessed
You claw at your belt and find no holy water.
The chapel font is still full, fool. Go BLESS
your courage before you waste my evening.
#unlock
#restart
:blessed
#play s+c+e+g+i
Holy water bursts across his brow. The Count
SHRIEKS, smoke boiling from cracked white skin.
He reels. His guard is down. STRIKE NOW.
#set weakened
#zap water
The vial is empty. He is reeling. Finish him.
#unlock
#restart
:strike
#if weakened #kill
Without holy water to stay him, he catches
your wrist mid-thrust and laughs in your face.
Cold. Wet. Then dark.
#unlock
#restart
:kill
#play tc+d+e+f+g+a+b+c
You drive the stake home. Bone gives. He howls
a howl five centuries old, then folds to ash.
The great east shutters crack. Grey light bleeds
in, and where the ash lies, nothing rises.
#set countdead
#give torches 1
Go north. Meet the dawn he feared so long.
#change object empty
#end
    end

    stat at 24,21 element Scroll cycle 1 under Empty color 0x00
    oop
@epitaph
Carved into the dais stone, half worn away:

$   HERE SLEEPS THE CRIMSON COUNT

He fears three things and three things only:
the blessed water, the sharpened stake,
and the sunrise he has not seen in an age.
Bring the first two. Let the third do the rest.
#end
    end

    stat at 29,21 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0x9D under Empty color 0x00
    oop
@font
#end
:touch
#play tcfc
A shallow stone basin, brimming with clear water
that faintly glows. The chapel's last blessing,
carried this far in a stoppered vial.
#if holy #already
You dip your vial. It fills, and warms your palm.
#give torches 0
#set holy
#end
:already
Your vial is already brimful. Steady, now.
#end
    end
  end
end

